@startuml
title OntoForge Local Workshop Architecture

actor "Operator / Claude Code" as Operator
actor "Browser viewer" as Browser
rectangle "Local workstation" {
  component "FastAPI server\nontology_workshop.server" as API
  database "Kuzu embedded graph\nworkshop.kuzu" as Kuzu
  component "Skill engine\nClaude API or offline rules" as Skills
  component "Report/export pipeline" as Export
  folder "exports/\nreports, snapshots, CSV" as Files
}
cloud "Anthropic Claude API\noptional external call" as Claude
cloud "Amazon Neptune target\nfuture deployment" as Neptune
cloud "S3 bulk-load bucket\nfuture deployment" as S3

Operator --> API : REST JSON\n/entity /relation /query
API --> Kuzu : validated openCypher\nread-only user queries
API --> Browser : WebSocket graph updates\noptional token auth
Browser --> API : local HTTPS/HTTP\nstatic UI + commands
API --> Skills : /skill execution
Skills --> Claude : HTTPS only\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API --> Export : report / snapshot / Neptune export
Export --> Files : constrained to ./exports\n0600 permissions
Files --> S3 : operator upload\nSSE-KMS + HTTPS-only
S3 --> Neptune : Bulk Loader IAM role

note right of API
Security boundary:
- local-only by default
- loopback access allowed without token
- ONTOFORGE_TOKEN gates non-loopback clients
- strict identifier validation
- read-only user Cypher
end note

note right of Neptune
Production guidance:
- private subnets
- AWS KMS encryption
- IAM database auth
- audit logs
end note
@enduml
